<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/U.S.-African-scientists-seek-biotech-answer-to-hunger" title="U.S., African scientists seek biotech answer to hunger" alt="link">U.S., African scientists seek biotech answer to hunger</a></h2>

	
					<p> Reuters, 27 March 2006. Article about a team of African scientists who will be working in Iowa over the next three years, tinkering with the genes of sorghum seeds. By taking genes from other crops as well as manipulating genes within the sorghum plant itself, scientists believe they can remake sorghum into a more easily digestible crop richer in vitamins A and E, iron, zinc and amino acids and protein.</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/04/2006</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/U.S.-African-scientists-seek-biotech-answer-to-hunger">Read more...</a>
