						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Food-security-concerns-pose-GMO-challenges-for-Southern-Africa" title="Food security concerns pose GMO challenges for Southern Africa " alt="link">Food security concerns pose GMO challenges for Southern Africa </a></h2>

	
					<p> Southern African News Features, 23 March 2006. Southern Africa is projecting a maize surplus of more than two million tonnes during the 2005/06 agricultural season but divergent views on genetically modified crops raise interesting questions about the role of intra-regional trade in bridging shortfalls in some SADC member states. Most countries have strict regulations governing GM organisms. South Africa, which has the biggest maize surplus, allows production and distribution of GMO food. This could have repercussions on domestic industry in most countries in the region.</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/04/2006</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Food-security-concerns-pose-GMO-challenges-for-Southern-Africa">Read more...</a>
