						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-FAO-website-helps-foresters-cope-with-invasive-species" title="New FAO website helps foresters cope with invasive species" alt="link">New FAO website helps foresters cope with invasive species</a></h2>

	
					<p> FAO, 20 February 2006. FAO has created a new online database and a <a href="http://www.fao.org/forestry/site/27082/en" target="_blank">website</a> to help foresters deal with the growing problem of invasive species introduced from foreign ecosystems. Invasive species are plants, animals or other organisms that move into an area where they didn’t traditionally live and out-compete native varieties, often with negative consequences for local ecosystems. But FAO’s new website and database include plants, woody species and vertebrates as well as insects, diseases and micro-organisms.</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/04/2006</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-FAO-website-helps-foresters-cope-with-invasive-species">Read more...</a>
