						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/An-EU-Strategy-for-Biofuels" title="An EU Strategy for Biofuels" alt="link">An EU Strategy for Biofuels</a></h2>

	
					<p> EC, 8 February 2006.The EU is supporting biofuels with the aim of reducing greenhouse gas emissions, boosting the decarbonisation of transport fuels, diversifying fuel supply sources, offering new income opportunities in rural areas and developing long-term replacements for fossil fuel. The Commission has adopted an EU Strategy for Biofuels along seven policy axes: stimulating demand for biofuels; capturing environmental benefits; developing the production and distribution of biofuels; expanding feedstock supplies; enhancing trade opportunities; supporting developing countries; and supporting research and development.</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/04/2006</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/An-EU-Strategy-for-Biofuels">Read more...</a>
